data.enText: to prevent sth from happening; to prevent a feeling from being expressed
She managed to stifle a yawn.

data.chText: 他们希望新规则不会压制创意。
data.enText: They hope the new rules will not stifle creativity.
The government failed to stifle the unrest.

data.chText: （使）窒息，无法自如地呼吸，感觉窒闷
data.enText: to feel unable to breathe, or to make sb unable to breathe, because it is too hot and/or there is no fresh air

data.chText: 在那间闷气的屋子里我感觉都快憋死了。
data.enText: I felt I was stifling in the airless room.

data.chText: 多数受害者是因烟雾窒息而死的。
data.enText: Most of the victims were stifled by the fumes.

data.chText: 闷得让人透不过气来的房间
“这里闷得人难受——我们能不能开一扇窗户？”
data.enText: ‘ It's stifling in here─can we open a window?’

data.chText: 她25岁时感到家庭生活令人窒息。
data.enText: At 25, she found family life stifling.

data.chText: 屋里热得人喘不上气来。

word_means: 窒息，无法自如地呼吸，感觉窒闷

means: (使)窒息，无法自如地呼吸，感觉窒闷

tr: joint between the femur and tibia in a quadruped

example: The child suffocated under the pillow

tr: impair the respiration of or obstruct the air passage of
example: The foul air was slowly suffocating the children

value.def: If someone stifles something you consider to be a good thing, they prevent it from continuing.

example.tran: 给孩子们定的各种规矩扼杀了他们的创造力。

example.ex: Critics have accused the US of trying to stifle debate.
example.tran: 批评家指责美国试图压制争论。

value.def: If you stifle a yawn or laugh, you prevent yourself from yawning or laughing.

example.ex: She makes no attempt to stifle a yawn...
His hand shot to his mouth to stifle a giggle.
example.tran: 他赶紧捂住嘴，不让自己笑出声来。

value.def: If you stifle your natural feelings or behaviour, you prevent yourself from having those feelings or behaving in that way.

example.ex: It is best to stifle curiosity and leave birds' nests alone...
example.tran: 最好能克制住好奇心，不要去碰鸟巢。

example.ex: He stifled his temptation to take hold of Ivy and shake her.
example.tran: 他压抑住想要抓住艾薇摇晃她的冲动。
